nd higher volume and other revenue-related expenses,  partially offset by productivity  savings,  lower  legal  expenses,  stranded  cost  reductions  and  lower transformation expenses in Corporate/Other.", score=1.6479297, metadata={'section': 'Citigroup', 'chunk_index': 13, 'page': 2}), ChunkResult(chunk_id='sec.gov_Archives_edgar_data_831001_000110465926042942_c-20260414xex99d1.htm_37_99306600', file_id='sec.gov_Archives_edgar_data_831001_000110465926042942_c-20260414xex99d1.htm', text='Markets (7)\nMarkets revenues of  $7.2  billion  increased  19%,  driven  by  growth  in  Fixed  Income  markets  and  Equity  markets revenues.\nFixed Income markets revenues of  $5.2  billion  increased  13%,  driven  by  growth  in  both  rates  and  currencies  and spread products and other fixed income. Rates and currencies revenues increased 6%, driven by revenue growth in the foreign exchange business on higher volumes and optimization of the balance sheet, largely offset by lower revenue in rates on elevated volatility. Spread products and other fixed income revenues increased 27%, primarily driven by strong performance in commodities.\nEquity  markets  revenues of  $2.1  billion  increased  39%,  driven  by  growth  in  derivatives,  prime  services  and  cash equities. Prime balances (8)  grew to a record and were up more than 50%.\nMarkets operating  expenses of $3.8 billion increased 11%,  primarily driven by higher performance-related compensation, higher volume-related expenses and higher legal expenses.', score=1.6649058, metadata={'section': 'Markets (7)', 'chunk_index': 37, 'page': 5}), ChunkResult(chunk_id='sec.gov_Archives_edgar_data_831001_000110465926042942_c-20260414xex99d1.htm_31_9c3e3416', file_id='sec.gov_Archives_edgar_data_831001_000110465926042942_c-20260414xex99d1.htm', text="Services (7)\n\n($ in millions, except as otherwise noted) Rates and currencies, 1Q'26 = 3,311. ($ in millions, except as otherwise noted) Rates and currencies, 4Q'25 = 2,449. ($ in millions, except as otherwise noted) Rates and currencies, 1Q'25 = 3,116. ($ in millions, except as otherwise noted) Rates and currencies, QoQ% = 35%. ($ in millions, except as otherwise noted) Rates and currencies, YoY% = 6%. Spread products / other fixed income, 1Q'26 = 1,855. Spread products / other fixed income, 4Q'25 = 1,105. Spread products / other fixed income, 1Q'25 = 1,462. Spread products / other fixed income, QoQ% = 68%. Spread products / other fixed income, YoY% = 27%. Fixed Income markets, 1Q'26 = 5,166. Fixed Income markets, 4Q'25 = 3,554. Fixed Income markets, 1Q'25 = 4,578. Fixed Income markets, QoQ% = 45%. Fixed", score=1.4505649, metadata={'section': 'Services (7)', 'page': 5, 'chunk_index': 31}), ChunkResult(chunk_id='sec.gov_Archives_edgar_data_831001_000110465926042942_c-20260414xex99d1.htm_1_d068b55f', file_id='sec.gov_Archives_edgar_data_831001_000110465926042942_c-20260414xex99d1.htm', text="RETURNED ~$7.4 BILLION IN THE FORM OF COMMON SHARE REPURCHASES AND COMMON DIVIDENDS\nPAYOUT RATIO OF 134%(3)\nCOMMON EQUITY TIER 1 CAPITAL RATIO OF 12.7%(4)\nBOOK VALUE PER SHARE OF $112.22\nTANGIBLE BOOK VALUE PER SHARE OF $99.01(5)\nNew  York,  April  14,  2026  -  Citigroup  Inc.  today  reported  net  income  for  the  first quarter 2026 of $5.8 billion, or $3.06 per diluted share, on revenues of $24.6 billion. This compares to net income of $4.1 billion, or $1.96 per diluted share, on revenues of $21.6 billion for the first quarter 2025.\nRevenues increased 14% (6)  from the prior-year period, driven by growth in each of Citi's five interconnected businesses (7)  and Legacy Franchises in All Other , as well as the impact of foreign exchange translation, partially offset by a decline in Corporate/Other, also in All Other .", score=1.5398109, metadata={'page': 1, 'section': 'RETURNED ~$7.4 BILLION IN THE FORM OF COMMON SHARE REPURCHASES AND COMMON DIVIDENDS', 'chunk_index': 1}), ChunkResult(chunk_id='sec.gov_Archives_edgar_data_831001_0001104659260